Definition: The container holding the specimen.  The recursive nature of containers; i.e. blood in tube in tray in rack is not addressed here.
Condition(s):
ele-1:All FHIR elements must have a @value or children {hasValue() or (children().count() > id.count())}
ext-1:Must have either extensions or value[x], not both {extension.exists() != value.exists()}

Definition: The device resource for the the container holding the specimen. If the container is in a holder then the referenced device will point to a parent device.
Requirements:
Element `Specimen.container.device` is part of an existing definition because parent element `Specimen.container` requires a cross-version extension.
Note that there is an externally-defined extension that has been flagged as the representation of FHIR R5 element `Specimen.container.device` with an unmapped Reference type: `http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/alternate-reference`.
Element `Specimen.container.device` has a context of Specimen.container based on following the parent source element upwards and mapping to `Specimen`.
Condition(s):
ele-1:All FHIR elements must have a @value or children {hasValue() or (children().count() > id.count())}
ext-1:Must have either extensions or value[x], not both {extension.exists() != value.exists()}
